	abstract = {Rohit Parikh has written on levels of knowledge (Parikh and Krasucki in Sadhana 17(1):167{\textendash}191, 1992). Levels of knowledge are relevant for the analysis of gossip protocols. Gossip protocols describe the dissemination of information over a network. We present some examples of epistemic gossip protocols, wherein the agents or processes communicate with each other by peer-to-peer contact (telephone calls), as in the usal gossip protocols, but wherein the decision to contact another agent is based on the calling agent{\textquoteright}s information only. This is, as far as we know, unusual in gossip protocols. In this we wish to honour Rohikh Parikh{\textquoteright}s long career and many contributions to logic and computer science.},
